Company Overview of The Swarthmore Group, Inc.



Snapshot People




Company Overview
The Swarthmore Group, Inc. is an employee owned investment manager. The firm primarily provides its services to pension and profit sharing plans and state or municipal government entities. It also caters to high net worth individuals, corporations, public entities, labor unions, foundations, and endowments. The firm manages separate client-focused equity and fixed income portfolios. It invests in the public equity and fixed income markets of the United States. The firm makes its equity investments in growth stocks of large-cap companies. It employs a fundamental analysis with a bottom-up stock picking approach to create its equity portfolio mix. The firm benchmarks the performance of its equ...
The Swarthmore Group, Inc. is an employee owned investment manager. The firm primarily provides its services to pension and profit sharing plans and state or municipal government entities. It also caters to high net worth individuals, corporations, public entities, labor unions, foundations, and endowments. The firm manages separate client-focused equity and fixed income portfolios. It invests in the public equity and fixed income markets of the United States. The firm makes its equity investments in growth stocks of large-cap companies. It employs a fundamental analysis with a bottom-up stock picking approach to create its equity portfolio mix. The firm benchmarks the performance of its equity portfolios against the S&P 500 Index and Russell 1000 Growth Index. The Swarthmore Group, Inc. was founded in 1991, and is based in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania.
Detailed Description


