Maxim Integrated Products (MXIM) : Swarthmore Group Inc Boosts Position by $20,576,379 – Highland Mirror      Home  Cover Story  Maxim Integrated Products (MXIM) : Swarthmore Group Inc Boosts Position by $20,576,379 Maxim Integrated Products (MXIM) : Swarthmore Group Inc Boosts Position by $20,576,379    January 13, 2017 ·  0      Maxim Integrated Products  (MXIM) : Swarthmore Group Inc  scooped up 506,650 additional shares in Maxim Integrated Products during the most recent quarter end , the firm said in a  disclosure report filed with the SEC on Jan 9, 2017. The investment management firm now holds a total of 517,775 shares of  Maxim Integrated Products which is valued at  $20,576,379.Maxim Integrated Products makes up approximately 3.02% of Swarthmore Group Inc’s portfolio.Other Hedge Funds, Including ,  Searle  added MXIM to its portfolio by purchasing 18,600 company shares during the most recent quarter which is  valued at  $739,164. Maxim Integrated Products makes up approx 0.21% of Searle’s portfolio.Ropes Wealth Advisors  boosted its stake in MXIM in the latest quarter, The investment management firm added 35 additional shares and now holds a total of 1,284 shares of  Maxim Integrated Products which is valued at  $51,026. Maxim Integrated Products makes up approx 0.02% of Ropes Wealth Advisors’s portfolio. Integrated Wealth Management  sold out all of its stake in MXIM during the most recent quarter. The investment firm sold 133 shares of  MXIM which is valued  $5,285.Eqis Capital Management  boosted its stake in MXIM in the latest quarter, The investment management firm added 6,550 additional shares and now holds a total of 18,434 shares of  Maxim Integrated Products which is valued at  $708,603. Maxim Integrated Products makes up approx 0.04% of Eqis Capital Management’s portfolio.Maxim Integrated Products Inc. is engaged in designing developing manufacturing and marketing a range of linear and mixed-signal integrated circuits referred to as analog circuits. The Company also provides a range of high-frequency process technologies and capabilities for use in custom designs. The Company’s products include switching regulators charge pumps linear regulators light-emitting diode drivers power switching transceivers level translators broadband switches current loop products real-time clocks data loggers and microcontrollers. The Company serves markets including communications and data center computing and consumer markets. Its communications and data center caters to base stations data storage servers telecommunications and other communications. Its computing caters to desktop computers notebook computers and peripherals. Its consumer products cater to smartphones digital cameras handheld computers home entertainment and appliances.Maxim Integrated Products closed down -0.23 points or -0.57% at $40.47 with 21,35,639 shares getting traded on Thursday. Post opening the session at $40.65, the shares hit an intraday low of $39.75 and an intraday high of $40.65 and the price fluctuated in this range throughout the day.Shares ended Thursday session in Red.On the company’s financial health, Maxim Integrated Products reported $0.48 EPS for the quarter, beating the analyst consensus estimate by $ 0.01 according to the earnings call on Oct 20, 2016. Analyst had a consensus of $0.47. The company had revenue of $561.40 million for the quarter, compared to analysts expectations of $560.39 million. The company’s revenue was down -.2 % compared to the same quarter last year.During the same quarter in the previous year, the company posted $0.25 EPS.Many Wall Street Analysts have commented on  Maxim Integrated Products. Maxim Integrated Products was Initiated by Loop Capital to “Buy” on Dec 6, 2016. Company shares were Reiterated by Drexel Hamilton on Oct 21, 2016 to “Buy”, Firm has raised the Price Target to $ 46 from a previous price target of $42 .         vedaVeda L is a technoholic geek, who loves financial stuff, and she's a PL-SQL 